---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Open Science Basics" description="Foundational resources and definitions for understanding Open Science.">
  <header class="masthead" style="background-image: url('/assets/img/background-image-blue.png'); background-size: cover; height: 40vh; min-height: 300px;">
    <div class="container h-100">
      <div class="row h-100 align-items-center justify-content-center text-center">
        <div class="col-lg-10 align-self-end">
          <h1 class="text-white font-weight-bold" style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);">Open Science Basics</h1>
          <hr class="divider my-4" style="border-color: #ffd100; border-width: 3px; max-width: 50px;" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-8 align-self-baseline">
          <p class="text-white-75 font-weight-light" style="text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);">
            Trusted definitions and frameworks to ground your understanding.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
          
          <div class="mb-5">
            <h2 class="section-heading">Getting Started</h2>
            <p class="lead text-muted">
              If you are new to Open Science, start with these reputable guides. They provide the "Why" and the "What" before you dive into the "How" of our curriculum.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- ACRL Cookbook -->
          <div class="card border-left-primary shadow-sm mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
              <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-start">
                  <h4 class="card-title text-primary">The ACRL Open Science Cookbook</h4>
                  <span class="badge badge-light border">Book / Reference</span>
              </div>
              <p class="card-text">
                A comprehensive collection of "recipes" for open science support. This is an essential companion to our curriculum, offering bite-sized case studies and how-to guides for librarians.
              </p>
              <a href="https://www.ala.org/news/2025/06/new-acrl-open-science-cookbook" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">
                  <i class="fas fa-book-open mr-1"></i> Read the Cookbook
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- NASA TOPS -->
          <div class="card border-left-info shadow-sm mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
              <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-start">
                  <h4 class="card-title text-info">NASA TOPS (Open Science 101)</h4>
                  <span class="badge badge-light border">Certification</span>
              </div>
              <p class="card-text">
                NASA's "Transform to Open Science" initiative. Their Open Science 101 curriculum is the gold standard for getting certified in core open science principles.
              </p>
              <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/open-science/training/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-info btn-sm">
                  <i class="fas fa-rocket mr-1"></i> Visit NASA TOPS
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="section-heading mt-5 mb-4">Foundational Frameworks</h3>

          <!-- UNESCO -->
          <div class="card border-left-dark shadow-sm mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h4 class="card-title">UNESCO Recommendation on Open Science</h4>
              <p class="card-text">
                The global standard defining Open Science as an inclusive construct combining open knowledge, infrastructure, and societal engagement.
              </p>
              <a href="https://www.unesco.org/en/open-science/about" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-dark btn-sm">Read the Recommendation</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAIR Principles -->
          <div class="card border-left-success shadow-sm mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h4 class="card-title text-success">The FAIR Principles</h4>
              <p class="card-text">
                Published in 2016, the FAIR principles are the dominant framework for research data management. They ensure data is machine-actionable.
              </p>
              <div class="row text-center my-3">
                <div class="col-3"><strong>F</strong>indable</div>
                <div class="col-3"><strong>A</strong>ccessible</div>
                <div class="col-3"><strong>I</strong>nteroperable</div>
                <div class="col-3"><strong>R</strong>eusable</div>
              </div>
              <a href="https://www.go-fair.org/fair-principles/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-success btn-sm">Explore FAIR</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- CARE Principles -->
          <div class="card border-left-warning shadow-sm mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h4 class="card-title text-warning" style="color: #d39e00 !important;">The CARE Principles for Indigenous Data Governance</h4>
              <p class="card-text">
                Developed by the Global Indigenous Data Alliance, CARE complements FAIR by focusing on the people and purpose behind the data.
              </p>
              <div class="row text-center my-3">
                <div class="col-3"><strong>C</strong>ollective Benefit</div>
                <div class="col-3"><strong>A</strong>uthority to Control</div>
                <div class="col-3"><strong>R</strong>esponsibility</div>
                <div class="col-3"><strong>E</strong>thics</div>
              </div>
              <a href="https://www.gida-global.org/care" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-warning btn-sm" style="color: #d39e00; border-color: #d39e00;">Explore CARE</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- NASA TOPS -->
          <div class="card border-left-info shadow-sm mb-5">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h4 class="card-title text-info">NASA TOPS (Transform to Open Science)</h4>
              <p class="card-text">
                NASA's initiative to spark a culture shift. Their "Open Science 101" curriculum is an excellent parallel resource for librarians looking for certification.
              </p>
              <a href="https://science.nasa.gov/open-science/training/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-info btn-sm">Visit NASA TOPS Training</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="my-5" />

          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="small text-muted mb-4">
                This project was made possible in part by the Institute of Museum and Library Services (Grant RE-252335-OLS-22).
            </p>
            <h2 class="section-heading">Ready to dive in?</h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-4">Now that you have the foundations, explore our librarian-focused curriculum.</p>
            <div class="row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="card bg-primary text-white border-0 shadow">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5>Start Teaching</h5>
                            <p class="small">Our lessons are CC-BY and ready for your next workshop.</p>
                            <a href="/#lessontab" class="btn btn-light btn-sm">Browse Lessons</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
.border-left-primary { border-left: 5px solid #007bff; }
.border-left-success { border-left: 5px solid #28a745; }
.border-left-warning { border-left: 5px solid #ffc107; }
.border-left-info { border-left: 5px solid #17a2b8; }
</style>
